CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 28, 1971, pg. 29, reads: "Boycott - Scenes as members of the United Farm Workers, Al-CIO started picketing a Pittsburgh outlet of Kentucky Fried Chicken in connection with a nationwide boycott against the firm in 40 states. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: United Farm Workers protesters, including Monsignor Charles Owen Rice, carrying signs reading "Colonel Sanders Unfair to Farm Workers," outside Kentucky Fried Chicken
